Telkom South Africa Declines to Comment on State Stake Sale Speculation

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-05-05T17:20:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/telkom-south-africa-declines-to-comment-on-state-stake-sale-speculation.html
Telkom  South Africa  Ltd. declined to
comment on a report by Talk Radio 702 saying there is
speculation that the about 40 percent stake in the company held
by the government will be sold to a Chinese investor.  “Telkom doesn’t comment on speculation,” Pynee Chetty, a
spokesman for the company, said in a telephone interview today.
Tiyani Rikhotso, a spokesman for South Africa’s communications
ministry, didn’t immediately respond to text and voice messages
left on his mobile phone.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
